11 An Act relating to state government; defining term;
prohibiting use of state funds for designated
12 purposes; prohibiting display of certain flags on
state property; providing for codification; providing
13 an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13001 of Title 74, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. As used in this section, "agency" means any agency, board,
21 commission, department, or other state government entity created
22 pursuant to the provisions of the Oklahoma Constitution or the
23 Oklahoma Statutes.
24
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
HB1219 HFLR Page 1
1 B. No funds may be used by any agency to develop, organize,
2 administer, engage in, promote, or endorse any activity, including
3 any event, initiative, official communication, social media post,
4 educational program, or public campaign, that aims to promote or
5 recognize Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender, Queer, and Intersex
6 Pride Month or any event with a similar theme.
7 C. Only flags pursuant to federal and state law may be
8 displayed by an agency on state property or grounds.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
10 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
11 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
12 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
13 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
14
15 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT OVERSIGHT, dated
03/10/2025 - DO PASS, As Amended and Coauthored.
